  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "As part of [pod safety](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/34160) for [StatefulSets](https://github.com/kubernetes/features/issues/137), we ensured that [kubectl drain uses the eviction subresource](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/34277) so it respects [PodDisruptionBudget](https://github.com/kubernetes/features/issues/85).\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, there is no script or recommended node upgrade process (AFAIK) that actually uses `kubectl drain`. In particular, the experimental [cluster/gce/upgrade.sh](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/cluster/gce/upgrade.sh) script uses GCE [rolling updates](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/33764) which simply terminate and recreate node VMs.\r\n\r\nThis issue is to track the need to provide a script or recommended process for upgrading nodes that actually respects PodDisruptionBudgets, so that the guarantees made by things like StatefulSet actually work during upgrades.\r\n\r\ncc @kubernetes/sig-apps",
